is getting his munition.

03:42.560 --> 03:43.959
It's clean.

03:44.360 --> 03:45.554
Meaning?

03:46.040 --> 03:47.996
Meaning it's untraceable.

03:48.600 --> 03:49.635
Your competitor's very smart.

03:50.800 --> 03:52.074
Get down!

04:08.960 --> 04:10.188
Fuck it.

05:33.240 --> 05:35.708
No one leaves the Fraternity, Cross.

05:36.120 --> 05:39.112
<i>I have a new perspective on the Fraternity.</i>

05:39.200 --> 05:40.599
Careful.

05:40.680 --> 05:44.434
You don't destroy something that's been
around for a thousand years.

05:44.520 --> 05:47.353
<i>It's already destroyed.</i>
<i>He broke the code.</i>

05:47.600 --> 05:49.511
<i>I have to stop this.</i>

05:49.600 --> 05:51.477
- Really?
<i>- You know this.</i>

05:52.560 --> 05:54.949
So why don't you face me yourself?

05:57.680 --> 05:59.955
Never send sheep to kill a wolf.

06:01.520 --> 06:03.476
<i>They were just the decoys.</i>

06:04.120 --> 06:05.712
<i>Goodbye, Mr X.</i>

06:38.080 --> 06:40.355
<i>Never send sheep to kill a wolf.</i>

06:40.440 --> 06:42.510
They were just the decoys.

06:43.840 --> 06:45.068
Wesley!

06:46.160 --> 06:47.195
What is it?

06:47.280 --> 06:49.077
What do you mean, "What is it"? Listen.

06:51.480 --> 06:55.189
Well, how am I suppose to sleep
with all that fucking racket?

06:55.800 --> 06:59.509
When are we gonna move so we don't
have to wake up to that shit?

06:59.600 --> 07:01.238
I kind of like it.

07:02.160 --> 07:05.994
<i>It helps to drown out the sound</i>
<i>of your annoying, fucking voice.</i>

07:06.080 --> 07:08.116
<i>Now, please, let me sleep.</i>

07:08.200 --> 07:10.509
Have you even thought about our talk?

07:10.600 --> 07:11.635
Yes.

07:12.840 --> 07:14.273
Which one?

07:15.720 --> 07:17.676
Perfect. That's perfect.

07:18.400 --> 07:19.992
Feed Annabelle.

08:03.440 --> 08:04.589
Sorry.

08:07.800 --> 08:09.711
Oh, my fucking God.

08:10.280 --> 08:13.431
I hope that's not my billing report
sitting on your desk.

08:13.520 --> 08:15.875
Holy shit on an altar, it is.

08:16.680 --> 08:19.513
I want that report on my desk in one hour.

08:19.600 --> 08:22.990
Okay, everybody,
we're all gonna stay an extra hour...

08:23.080 --> 08:24.991
<i>Want to hear something sad?</i>

08:25.080 --> 08:29.551
<i>I need an ergonomic keyboard</i>
<i>to keep my repetitive stress injury in check.</i>

08:29.640 --> 08:33.996
<i>Just the fact that I repeat something enough</i>
<i>that it causes me stress is fucking sad.</i>

08:34.080 --> 08:36.275
Nice job, dude. You seen Barry?

08:37.559 --> 08:39.994
He had to go to the dentist. Again.

08:41.840 --> 08:42.828
Yes!

08:44.159 --> 08:45.229
Barry!

08:49.080 --> 08:51.469
You think they have that
morning-after pill here?

08:51.560 --> 08:53.073
That thing works.
Crush it up, put it in her omelette,

08:53.160 --> 08:56.869
"Hey, baby, breakfast in bed."
You can never be too safe.

08:56.960 --> 08:58.359
Oh, God.

08:59.360 --> 09:01.510
I lost my wallet somewhere.

09:03.520 --> 09:05.192
All this together?

09:06.160 --> 09:07.832
- No, no.
- Yes.

09:09.800 --> 09:11.233
He is the man.

09:11.320 --> 09:13.550
- How much is it?
- Oh. Plus this.

09:14.640 --> 09:15.834
$20.42.

09:16.920 --> 09:18.273
Watermelon.

09:19.640 --> 09:21.119
Chicks dig it.

09:24.000 --> 09:24.989
Thanks.

09:25.440 --> 09:26.475
See you next time.

09:26.560 --> 09:27.595
Have a good night.

09:27.680 --> 09:29.159
I love these energy drinks, man.

09:29.240 --> 09:32.073
I'm almost, like, kind of on
an energy drink cleanse,

09:32.160 --> 09:35.152
where I do one for breakfast
and then, like, two or three for lunch.

09:35.240 --> 09:36.468
<i>I'm the man?</i>

09:36.560 --> 09:38.710
<i> Yeah, right, Barry, I'm the man.</i>

09:38.800 --> 09:40.153
<i>In fact, I'm so much the man,</i>

09:40.240 --> 09:44.756
<i>I have a standing prescription for</i>
<i>medication to control my anxiety attacks.</i>

09:45.240 --> 09:47.800
<i>God, I wish I had something else</i>
<i>to relieve my stress.</i>

09:47.880 --> 09:49.393
Hello, Wesley.

09:51.960 --> 09:54.952
<i>You know, there are people,</i>
<i>beautiful people,</i>

09:55.040 --> 09:58.635
<i>you just wish they could see you</i>
<i>in a different setting, a different place,</i>

09:58.720 --> 10:01.075
<i>instead of where you are,</i>
<i>what you've become.</i>

10:01.160 --> 10:02.798
Nicole is so hot.

10:04.200 --> 10:05.428
What?

10:06.280 --> 10:08.271
Boom goes the dynamite.

10:08.360 --> 10:11.113
<i>But most of all,</i>
<i>you wish you weren't such a pussy</i>

10:11.200 --> 10:14.192
<i>for wishing for things</i>
<i>that will never change.</i>

10:16.760 --> 10:19.638
Good God A'mighty, you're over
here like it's spring fucking break,

10:19.720 --> 10:21.915
and I still don't have that billing report.

10:22.000 --> 10:24.468
Why do I even keep you around, Wesley?

10:25.160 --> 10:26.798
I'll get it done, Janice.

10:26.880 --> 10:30.236
Like I never heard that before.
"I'll get it done."

10:31.400 --> 10:33.436
"I'll get it done. I'll get it done, Janice.

10:33.520 --> 10:35.192
"I'll get it done."

10:46.080 --> 10:49.231
Why don't you have anything
to say for yourself?

10:49.680 --> 10:52.114
I'm sorry.

10:52.800 --> 10:54.199
Well, you're worthless.

10:54.280 --> 10:57.158
I'm the one who's sorry I hired your ass.

11:21.600 --> 11:24.910
<i>You know what the best thing is</i>
<i>about the end of the day?</i>

11:25.000 --> 11:27.833
<i>Tomorrow it starts all over again.</i>

12:36.760 --> 12:38.671
- Hi. How you doing?
- Good.

12:51.160 --> 12:53.628
- I'm sorry?
- You apologise too much.

12:57.400 --> 12:59.118
Sorry about that.

13:07.120 --> 13:08.917
I knew your father.

13:12.360 --> 13:15.113
My father left the week I was born, so...

13:16.120 --> 13:20.193
Your father died yesterday on the rooftop
of the Metropolitan Building.

13:20.280 --> 13:21.554
Sorry.

13:27.600 --> 13:29.238
Look, the liquor rounds
are just over there, so...

13:29.320 --> 13:31.834
Your father was one of the greatest
assassins who ever lived.

13:31.920 --> 13:34.434
The man who killed him is behind you.

14:49.400 --> 14:51.311
This guy's just shooting up...

14:58.880 --> 15:00.313
Sorry. Sorry.

15:25.160 --> 15:28.948
What... Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
What the fuck just happened?

15:32.520 --> 15:34.715
Please! Please! Please drive faster.

15:34.800 --> 15:36.597
- Please be quiet.
- Please drive... Please drive faster.

15:36.680 --> 15:39.990
Please... Please understand
that I care about my life!

15:44.960 --> 15:47.076
I don't know what the fuck
you did to piss this guy off,

15:47.160 --> 15:49.116
but you're gonna have to let me out
and call the cops!

15:51.880 --> 15:53.108
Hey! Hey!

15:56.720 --> 16:00.315
What are you doing? Oh, shit!
Are you crazy?

16:04.120 --> 16:05.394
Oh, shit!

16:10.520 --> 16:12.476
I think we lost him. I think we lost him.

16:12.560 --> 16:15.597
Could you let me out
at the next corner, please?

16:16.960 --> 16:18.188
Shit!

16:21.040 --> 16:22.029
Fuck!

16:24.400 --> 16:26.038
Oh, shit!

16:28.160 --> 16:29.752
He's right there!

16:40.640 --> 16:43.677
Look, I'm an accountant.
I'm just an accountant.

16:44.960 --> 16:46.632
Oh, fuck!

16:49.280 --> 16:51.635
He's fucking persistent, you know.

16:53.000 --> 16:54.115
Fuck!

17:01.280 --> 17:03.032
You kick his ass!

17:07.680 --> 17:08.954
Shoot him!

17:10.119 --> 17:13.907
What are you doing?
What are you shooting our car for, huh?

17:15.560 --> 17:18.233
- Are you crazy?
- Grab the wheel.

17:18.880 --> 17:20.632
Where are you going?

17:22.240 --> 17:23.832
Get back in here!

17:25.240 --> 17:27.800
Oh, my God!

17:42.840 --> 17:44.796
Oh, damn! I'm sorry.

17:54.000 --> 17:55.399
- Gun!
- What?

17:58.000 --> 17:59.558
Under the seat!

17:59.640 --> 18:00.709
Here.

18:26.240 --> 18:27.514
Oh, shit!

18:30.080 --> 18:31.832
Shit!

18:37.760 --> 18:38.749
- Look out!
- Get out!

18:38.840 --> 18:40.990
Look out! Oh, my God!

18:41.080 --> 18:42.274
Shit!

18:49.880 --> 18:54.590
I'm sorry!

19:12.480 --> 19:13.959
Behind you!

20:38.240 --> 20:39.434
Fuck.

20:42.880 --> 20:44.199
Shit. Shit.

20:46.200 --> 20:47.349
Hello.

20:48.280 --> 20:50.510
I don't have any money or...

20:51.680 --> 20:53.432
I thought he'd be

20:53.720 --> 20:55.073
taller.

20:56.200 --> 20:57.428
Taller?

20:58.720 --> 20:59.914
Sir...

21:00.800 --> 21:05.112
Sir, I've been trying to explain
to the lady here that I'm an accountant.

21:05.200 --> 21:08.749
I'm an account service representative...
I'm an account manager.

21:08.840 --> 21:11.673
And I'm sure that if you call
my boss, Janice,

21:11.760 --> 21:14.513
she'd fill you in on whatever
has gone wrong.

21:14.600 --> 21:17.717
You can contact her by email or...
She'll put you straight.

21:17.800 --> 21:19.950
Shoot the wings off the flies.

21:20.880 --> 21:23.030
I don't know what that means.

21:23.720 --> 21:26.837
Shoot the wings off the flies.

21:31.360 --> 21:34.750
I really think you have me mixed up
with somebody else.

21:36.200 --> 21:37.553
On three.

21:38.040 --> 21:40.235
Either you shoot, or I do.

21:51.120 --> 21:52.235
One.

21:55.240 --> 21:56.355
Okay.

22:02.680 --> 22:03.749
Two.

22:03.840 --> 22:05.796
I can't even see them!

22:11.120 --> 22:12.314
Three.

22:29.080 --> 22:30.593
Okay. Okay.

22:50.840 --> 22:51.829
That's impossible.

22:51.920 --> 22:55.230
A lot of things for you
weren't possible before today.

22:55.960 --> 22:59.077
What you experienced, Wesley,
was not a panic attack.

22:59.720 --> 23:03.349
Your heart was beating in excess of
400 beats per minute,

23:03.440 --> 23:06.034
sending abundant amounts of
adrenaline into your bloodstream.

23:06.120 --> 23:09.157
This allows you to see and react faster
than normal.

23:09.240 --> 23:12.038
Only a few people in the world can do that.

23:12.400 --> 23:15.312
Your father could do it and you can do it.

23:16.240 --> 23:19.630
With a little work,
you can learn to control these attacks.

23:19.720 --> 23:21.438
Stay away from me.

23:22.160 --> 23:23.513
Just stay back from me.

23:23.600 --> 23:25.795
I have a gun, sir. All right?

23:27.680 --> 23:29.272
My name is Sloan.

23:30.120 --> 23:31.519
This is Fox.

23:31.920 --> 23:35.117
And the others you see around you
are all very good at killing.

23:35.200 --> 23:37.430
So, if I were you,
I'd keep the gun pointed at me.

23:37.520 --> 23:39.476
You don't wanna point it at any of them.

23:39.560 --> 23:41.073
That's better.

23:41.160 --> 23:42.513
- You're insane.
- No.

23:42.600 --> 23:44.591
Insanity is wasting your life as a nothing

23:44.680 --> 23:46.955
when you have the blood of a killer
flowing in your veins.

23:47.040 --> 23:50.396
Insanity is being shit on, beat down,

23:50.840 --> 23:52.831
coasting through life
in a miserable existence

23:52.920 --> 23:56.833
when you have a caged lion locked inside
and a key to release it.

23:57.960 --> 24:02.158
This gun you're holding is an Imanishi 17.
It belonged to your father.

24:03.240 --> 24:05.993
He could conduct
a symphony orchestra with it.

24:06.080 --> 24:09.914
And you're going to use it to kill the man
who shot him down in cold blood.

24:10.000 --> 24:13.595
- I can't...
- The same man who tried to kill you tonight.

24:16.160 --> 24:18.355
Your father was one of us.

24:18.440 --> 24:22.069
A fraternity of assassins.
The weapons of fate.

24:23.440 --> 24:26.398
We've transferred all of his assets
over to you.

24:26.480 --> 24:29.756
And let me assure you, they are substantial.

24:31.920 --> 24:35.196
It is your long-awaited destiny

24:35.280 --> 24:36.679
to join us.

24:48.600 --> 24:50.830
Back off. Back off.

24:52.520 --> 24:54.875
You don't know anything about me.

24:55.200 --> 24:57.919
Stay away from me. Stay away from me.

24:58.000 --> 25:00.036
You stay away from me?

25:00.120 --> 25:03.237
You stay away from me, please?
Will you let me through?

25:33.440 --> 25:36.750
<i>You know when you have a dream</i>
<i>and you're half awake,</i>

25:36.840 --> 25:38.796
<i>but it's still in the fringe of your brain?</i>

25:38.880 --> 25:42.509
<i>Then you open your eyes</i>
<i>and you're so damn glad it was a dream.</i>

25:49.880 --> 25:51.916
<i>This was nothing like that.</i>

26:17.320 --> 26:20.232
I'm sorry. Could you just give me
one second? Thank you.

26:29.520 --> 26:30.748
Oh, shit.

26:40.760 --> 26:41.954
Wesley.

26:45.920 --> 26:47.672
What's up with you?

26:48.200 --> 26:49.872
What do you mean?

26:50.560 --> 26:53.120
You're... You're here early.

26:56.000 --> 26:57.672
Is... You seem a little pepped up.

26:57.760 --> 27:00.149
- You all right?
- Well, yeah.

27:01.040 --> 27:02.155
Yeah.

27:03.000 --> 27:04.672
I guess I feel

27:05.640 --> 27:07.517
kind of different.

27:08.000 --> 27:10.560
Whatever. I'm gonna go get
some Post-it Notes. Do you want one?

27:10.640 --> 27:11.675
- No.
- Really?

27:11.760 --> 27:13.432
- Yeah.
- Okay.

27:26.960 --> 27:30.555
Jesus H. fucking Popsicle,
I still don't have my billing reports,

27:30.640 --> 27:33.438
but you've got time to sit here
and Google your ass off.

27:33.520 --> 27:34.999
Well, I know one thing.

27:35.080 --> 27:37.435
You've got your review
coming up next week,

27:37.520 --> 27:41.672
and I can't wait to start checking me off
some big fucking boxes.

27:41.760 --> 27:44.638
Attitude, poor! Performance, poor!

27:45.880 --> 27:47.836
Management skills, poor!

27:47.920 --> 27:51.071
Works well with others.
That's a fucking joke.

27:52.240 --> 27:54.674
What is this bullshit? Who's this prick?

27:54.760 --> 27:57.593
Some loser gets his head blown off
at the Metropolitan...

27:57.680 --> 27:59.796
Shut the fuck up!

28:07.440 --> 28:10.796
She has one single iota of tenuous power.

28:10.880 --> 28:13.599
She thinks she can push everyone around.

28:14.960 --> 28:16.712
You don't need this.

28:20.800 --> 28:22.233
I understand.

28:24.040 --> 28:26.873
Junior high must have been kind of tough,

28:26.960 --> 28:30.430
but it doesn't give you the right to treat
your workers like horseshit, Janice.

28:30.520 --> 28:32.795
I know we laugh at you, Janice.

28:33.280 --> 28:36.636
We all know you keep your stash of jelly
doughnuts in the top drawer of your desk.

28:36.720 --> 28:38.711
But I want you to know

28:39.200 --> 28:43.159
if you weren't such a bitch,
we'd feel sorry for you.

28:45.440 --> 28:47.351
I do feel sorry for you.

28:48.280 --> 28:51.033
But as it stands, the way you behave,

28:51.840 --> 28:54.673
I feel I can speak for the entire office

28:55.200 --> 28:57.031
when I tell you

28:58.040 --> 28:59.758
go fuck yourself.

29:13.840 --> 29:16.559
Yeah. That was great, bro. Who's the man?

29:23.720 --> 29:24.789
I'm the man.

30:01.280 --> 30:03.191
That's a bad idea.

30:05.320 --> 30:06.878
Couldn't find your keys, huh?

30:06.960 --> 30:08.632
That could be handy.
You going to teach me that?

30:08.720 --> 30:10.358
I might need that.

30:11.280 --> 30:14.431
So, Fox, right? What is that?
Is that a call sign?

30:14.520 --> 30:17.114
Is it like Maverick in <i>Top Gun?</i>

30:17.640 --> 30:20.108
You could tell me,
but you'd have to kill me?

30:20.200 --> 30:21.918
I'm just kidding.

31:29.840 --> 31:31.034
Peter!

31:32.800 --> 31:36.918
Check the shuttle rotation on this STB.
It should be 300 per minute.

31:37.200 --> 31:40.397
This kind of cotton weave,
the opposing thread count should be 4,000.

31:40.480 --> 31:43.756
Hey, this is pretty awesome, huh?

31:45.120 --> 31:46.599
Is it a front?

31:48.480 --> 31:50.994
- Front for what?
- I don't know.

31:51.080 --> 31:52.559
Assassinations.

31:53.720 --> 31:56.632
You may think this is a front for something,

31:57.440 --> 32:00.318
all I can tell you is this is a textile mill.

32:00.400 --> 32:03.198
And George...
George, go help Peter up there.

32:03.280 --> 32:04.349
Yeah.

32:05.760 --> 32:07.557
This is a textile mill.

32:08.000 --> 32:09.069
And a damn good one.

32:09.160 --> 32:11.833
Yeah, that's cute,
but that's bullshit, right?

32:11.920 --> 32:15.037
I mean, all these guys are killers,
aren't they?

32:17.280 --> 32:19.316
I think you owe me some answers.

32:19.800 --> 32:22.360
All right. Clearly I don't understand,

32:22.440 --> 32:25.159
but do you make sweaters
or do you kill people?

32:44.880 --> 32:47.838
That's an awful lot of questions over coffee.

32:56.480 --> 32:58.596
Are you sure you're ready for the answers?

32:58.680 --> 33:00.272
Yes, I'm sure.

33:01.160 --> 33:02.912
I can't go back.

33:03.000 --> 33:04.592
Not to my life.

33:08.960 --> 33:10.473
He's all yours.

33:11.360 --> 33:13.112
All right. We're up.

33:23.480 --> 33:24.993
How you doing?

33:26.080 --> 33:27.593
